cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the deployment of wireless networks and the optimization of spectrum allocation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the efficient utilization of resources, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of radio access network slicing and dynamic spectrum allocation policies could also be considered as a system-level approach, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper mentions simulation results, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
